# Build_And_Release

## 1. Applies when
Always. Build and release process is required for any shipped product.

## 2. This document owns
Build pipeline: compilation, cooking, packaging, and staging; version numbering scheme and branch strategy; release candidate criteria and sign-off process; platform-specific build requirements and submission checklists; patch and hotfix deployment process; continuous integration and continuous delivery (CI/CD) configuration; build artifact storage, distribution, and retention policies.

## 3. This document does NOT own
QA testing of builds (→ QA_Test_Plan); feature content included in a release (→ Production_Roadmap); code architecture and module dependencies (→ Technical_Design); release notes and changelogs (→ coordinated with all design docs).

## 4. Recommended chapter structure
1. Build Pipeline · 2. Versioning & Branch Strategy · 3. Release Candidate Criteria · 4. Platform Submission Checklists · 5. Patch & Hotfix Process · 6. CI/CD Configuration · 7. Artifact Storage & Distribution

## 5. Common boundaries
- Build owns "how it's assembled"; QA owns "whether it passes".
- Version numbering lives here; version history lives in changelogs.
- Platform submission checklists reference compliance from QA_Test_Plan.

## 6. Common audit rules
- Check that build pipeline references project structure docs.
- Check that version scheme is consistent with tag / CHANGELOG conventions.
